0and%2016%20to%20users%20who%20are%20not%20%22publishers%22%20but%20share%20news%20and%20current%20affairs%20content%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20bring%20both%20intermediaries%20and%20user-generated%20news%20under%20the%20MIB%27s%20blocking%20powers%20and%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20the%20Inter-Departmental%20Committee%20(IDC)%20under%20Part%20III%20of%20the%20IT%20Rules%2C%202021s.%0A%0ARecommendation%3A%20This%20proposed%20amendment%20must%20be%20withdrawn%20entirely.%20Any%20regulation%20of%20user-generated%20content%20should%20follow%20established%20legal%20processes%2C%20including%20those%20under%20Section%2069A%20of%20the%20IT%20Act%2C%20and%20should%20not%20be%20routed%20through%20indirect%20mechanisms.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20scope%20of%20Rule%208(1)%20should%20be%20restricted%20to%20publishers%2C%20as%20originally%20intended%2C%20and%20should%20not%20extend%20to%20user-generated%20content%20on%20intermediary%20platforms.%20Therefore%2C%20such%20amendment%20to%20the%20proviso%20should%20be%20withdrawn%20in%20its%20entirety.%0A%0A4.%20Rule%2014%20to%20expand%20the%20scope%20and%20functioning%20of%20the%20IDC%20to%20hear%20%22matters%22%20referred%20by%20MIB%3A%0A%E2%97%8F%20Rule%2014(2)%20presently%20requires%20the%20IDC%20to%20hear%20%22complaints%20regarding%20violation%20or%20contravention%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Ethics%22.%20These%20are%20complaints%20and%20grievances%20from%20users.%0A%E2%97%8F%20The%20IDC%20now%20hears%3A%20(a)%20grievances%20arising%20from%20decisions%20at%20Level%20I%20or%20II%20(from%20users)%3B%20or%20(b)%20%22matters%22%20referred%20to%20by%20the%20Ministry.%20Clause%20(b)%20is%20unconstrained%20since%3A%0Ai.%20there%20is%20no%20requirement%20that%20the%20%22matter%22%20arise%20from%20a%20complaint%2C%0Aii.%20no%20requirement%20that%20the%20%22matter%22%20relate%20to%20a%20Code%20of%20Ethics%20violation%3B%20and%0Aiii.%20no%20requirement%20that%20the%20affected%20party%20be%20heard%20before%20the%20referral.%0A%E2%97%8F%20The%20IDC%20effectively%20now%20operates%20as%20a%20free-standing%20censorship%20committee%20that%20can%20take%20up%20%22matters%22%20referred%20to%20by%20the%20executive.%20Given%20the%20current%20surge%20in%20takedown%20notices%20this%20year%2C%20such%20expansion%20raises%20further%20concerns%20on%20the%20freedom%20of%20speech%20enumerated%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%0A%0ARecommendation%3A%20This%20proposed%20amendment%20must%20be%20withdrawn%20entirely.%20Section%2069A%20and%20Section%2079%20of%20the%20IT%20Act%20are%20the%20two%20provisions%20that%20allow%20for%20blocking%20mechanisms.%20Section%2069A%20provides%20for%20the%20original%20blocking%20mechanism%20and%20Section%2079%20acts%20as%20an%20exemption%20provision%20(not%20an%20independent%20censorship%20mechanism).%20The%20minimal%20procedural%20safeguards%20enumerated%20under%20Section%2069A%20are%20already%20being%20diluted.%20First%2C%20the%20government%20is%20increasingly%20relying%20on%20Section%2079(3)(b)%20of%20the%20IT%20Act%2C%20read%20with%20Rule%203(1)(d)%20of%20the%20IT%20Rules%2C%202021s%2C%20to%20compel%20intermediaries%20to%20remove%20content.%20On%20top%20of%20it%20the%20current%20draft%20amendments%20allow%20the%20IDC%20to%20now%20operate%20as%20a%20free-standing%20censorship%20committee%20that%20can%20take%20up%20%22matters%22%20referred%20to%20by%20the%20executive.%20Together%2C%20this%20forms%20a%20chilling%20effect%2C%20this%20means%20that%20people%20may%20refrain%20from%20expressing%20themselves%20online%20due%20to%20the%20fear%20of%20their%20content%20or%20entire%20account%20being%20taken%20down.%20Such%20a%20climate%20not%20only%20erodes%20individual%20liberty%20but%20also%20dilutes%20the%20essence%20of%20democracy%20by%20curbing%20public%20debate%2C%20criticism%2C%20and%20activism.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20MeitY%20must%20withdraw%20this%20proposed%20amendment%20in%20its%20entirety.%0A%0ABest%20Regards%2C%0A%5BName%5D"
